    &lt;Title&gt;Awful experience would avoid this hospital at all costs&lt;/Title&gt;
    &lt;ScreenName&gt;Matthew Lawson&lt;/ScreenName&gt;
    &lt;CommentText&gt;I was admitted to the AMU ward after receiveing excellent treatment in A&amp;amp;amp;E for Shortness of breath. On arriveing at AMU i noticed their was only one pillow very flat pillow on my bed i asked for another pillow but i was told their was none. I explained i would not be able to sleep in the bed as i have to have the bed flat due to haveing spinal stenosis and need to be propped up with pillows due to my respitory problems. I knew straight away that i did not want to stay in. I advised the nurseing staff that i wanted to go home and she got the dr to come and speak to me. He then placed me on a section 5.2 which prevented me from leaveing for 72 hours this caused me to feel very anxious and i did not know what was going to happen next. They also had security guards watching me and following me. I noticed on my arrival to the ward their was a large number of security guards on the ward which made my anxiety worse. The 2 nice nurses that were on duty in my bay area were very kind and one of them let me go into the tv room which a secuirty guard was asleep but left on my arrival. I managed to relax a bit more then i was told quite rudely by a hca that i would have to go back to my own bed area. I suffer from severe anxiety centred around hospitals and being sectioned it this situation made me a lot worse. As soon as the psychiatrist released me from the section 5.2 i took my own discharge. I would not remmomend this hospital to anyone and i will never return.&lt;/CommentText&gt;
